description: Split status model for applications (application/payment/fulfillment + automation jobs)
alwaysApply: true
---

# Application state machine (split statuses)

- Do **not** use one giant “status enum”. Split into:
  - `applicationStatus` (user-facing lifecycle)
  - `paymentStatus` (money movement)
  - `fulfillmentStatus` (ops execution)
  - `automationJobs` (attempts/artifacts) as separate records
- Client UI maps internal states to **neutral** language (no “automation failed”, no affiliate details).
- Never encode payment events as “application status only”; keep payment transitions consistent with webhooks.

